LOG_NORMAL_PRIOR_PARSER

public static XMLObjectParser LOG_NORMAL_PRIOR_PARSER
A special parser that reads a convenient short form of priors on parameters.

If X ~ logNormal, then log(X) ~ Normal.

If meanInRealSpace=false, mean specifies the mean of log(X) and stdev specifies the standard deviation of log(X).

If meanInRealSpace=true, mean specifies the mean of X, but stdev specifies the standard deviation of log(X).
